<br>
I've been doing some testing and want someone to explain the &quot;Haste equals Damage dished out&quot; comment.<br>
<br>
With only 1 Lam equipped at 0 haste I attack 46 times per minute.<br>
<br>
With only 1 Lam equipped at 66% haste I attack 77 times per minute.<br>
<br>
So haste equals more attacks. This should result in more dmg but haste in and of itself does not equal more dmg.<br>
<br>
This testing also blows away the minimum weapon delay of 10 theroy. If it were true the max attacks per minute would be 60. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utenakha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenakha</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/9/01 12:01:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste</span><hr size=1> There is no minimum weapon delay.  Haste inreases your rate of attacks and hence your damage and your taunting. <p>Gorlab 56 Warrior<BR>
Tenakha 52 Druid<BR>
Keepers of the Faith</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uiuldiin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iuldiin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/01 8:14:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste</span><hr size=1> Ignor this... <p>-Iuldiin</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uiuldiin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iuldiin</A> at: 3/12/01 8:15:02 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uravikbladestorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravik Bladestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/01 11:42:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste</span><hr size=1> To answer your question Nazdul your Jade Mace would become a 9/12 weapon with 60% haste. Here is the math.<br>
<br>
60+100=160, 100/160=.625, .625x18=11.25 (12 rounded up)<br>
<br>
This is using Draky's formula, which is pretty darn close to what I have been able to calculate.<br>
<br>
Klunc I think I have the math to help you understand what haste is doing for you.<br>
<br>
46 attacks per minute<br>
77 attacks per minute @ 66% haste<br>
Lets make two assumptions then toss in some algebra  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Assumption one, Lammy attacks 31 times per minute (delay of 19 means one attack every 1.9 seconds)<br>
Assumption two, the other 15 attacks are double attacks.<br>
<br>
First let us get a ratio of double attacks to primary.<br>
<br>
15/31=.48<br>
<br>
Second let us work Draky's magic on the Lammy's delay.<br>
66+100=166, 100/166=.60, 19x.60=11.4 (this gives us one attack every 1.14 seconds)<br>
<br>
Now let us look at Lammy with 66% haste.<br>
<br>
60/1.14=52 attacks per minute <br>
52x.48=25 double attacks per minute<br>
<br>
52+25=77    TADAAA  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
